# Access Control Vulnerability Lab

## Overview

This repository contains my solution and notes for a PortSwigger Web Security Academy Access Control Vulnerability Lab. The lab focuses on identifying and exploiting authorization flaws that allow unauthorized users to access restricted resources or functionality.

## Objective

* Identify access control weaknesses.
* Analyze how authorization mechanisms are implemented.
* Exploit the vulnerability to gain unauthorized access.
* Understand the security impact of broken access controls.

## Key Learning Points

* Access control vulnerabilities occur when applications fail to properly enforce user permissions.
* Broken authorization can expose sensitive data and privileged functionality.
* Server-side authorization checks are critical for protecting sensitive resources.
* Proper role-based access control (RBAC) and validation mechanisms help prevent unauthorized access.

